articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: U.S. Secretary of State Blinken took shelter with Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu in a bunker during an air raid alert as the U.S. top diplomat worked on making progress to ease the humanitarian crisis in Gaza.
articles.title: Israel and Hamas at war: Latest news

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Jordan's King Abdullah on Tuesday warned against trying to push Palestinian refugees into Egypt or Jordan, adding that the humanitarian situation must to be dealt with inside Gaza and the West Bank.
articles.title: King Abdullah on Gaza: 'No refugees in Jordan, no refugees in Egypt'

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli air strike killed senior Hamas armed commander Ayman Nofal in Gaza, the Hamas armed wing Izz el-Deen Al-Qassam Brigades said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Israeli air strike kills senior Hamas armed commander Ayman Nofal in Gaza

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Israeli military is getting ready for the next phase of its campaign against the Gaza Strip but plans may not conform to widespread expectations of an imminent ground offensive, an army spokesperson said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Israeli army spokesman says next phase of war may be different from expectations

articles.author: Michelle Nichols
articles.description: The United Nations warned on Tuesday that Palestinian civilians in the Gaza Strip are being "packed into an ever-smaller area" and life-saving essentials have essentially run out, appealing for a humanitarian truce to allow aid access.
articles.title: UN warns Gaza civilians being 'packed in ever-smaller area'

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Dozens of U.S. citizens from Israel arrived in Cyprus early Tuesday on the first evacuation boat organised by the United States amid the escalating crisis in the Middle East.
articles.title: First batch of U.S. citizens leaving Israel arrive in Cyprus by boat

articles.author: Nicole Jao
articles.description: Oil prices edged higher on Tuesday as investors wait to see if U.S. diplomatic efforts and a trip by President Joe Biden to Israel will prevent the conflict in the Middle East from widening.
articles.title: Oil prices edge higher ahead of Biden Middle East trip

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: An Israeli air strike on Tuesday killed hundreds of Palestinians at a Gaza City hospital crammed with patients and displaced people, health authorities in the besieged enclave said.
articles.title: Israeli air strike hits Gaza hospital, hundreds dead, health officials say

articles.author: Dan Williams
articles.description: One Israeli cabinet minister was barred from a hospital visitors' entrance. Another's bodyguards were drenched with coffee thrown by a bereaved man. A third had "traitor" and "imbecile" shouted at her as she came to comfort families evacuated during the horror.
articles.title: Whatever unfolds in Gaza war, judgment day looms for Netanyahu

articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: A group representing General Motors (GM.N), Toyota Motor (7203.T), Volkswagen (VOWG_p.DE) and nearly all other major automakers on Monday sharply criticized the Biden administration proposal to drastically hike fuel efficiency requirements.
articles.title: Automakers blast US plan to hike fuel efficiency rules
